--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                          INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Successfully installing Frama-C and PathCrawler is a prerequisite to StaDy.
KLEE is not required, although StaDy may be able to interact with it in the
future.



================================================================================
                                FRAMA-C
================================================================================

$ git clone git@git.frama-c.com:frama-c/frama-c.git
$ cd frama-c
$ ./configure
$ make
$ sudo make install
$ cd ..


================================================================================
                            PATHCRAWLER (closed source)
================================================================================

$ git clone git@git.frama-c.com:pathcrawler/pathcrawler.git
$ cd pathcrawler
$ autoconf
$ ./configure
$ make
$ sudo make install
$ cd ..


================================================================================
                   KLEE (out-of-date but self-contained package)
================================================================================

$ sudo apt-get install cde

Download the self-contained package:
   http://keeda.stanford.edu/~pgbovine/klee-cde-package.v2.tar.bz2 (dead?)

$ export PATH=".../klee-cde-package/bin":$PATH
$ export C_INCLUDE_PATH=".../klee-cde-package/cde-root/home/pgbovine/klee/include":$C_INCLUDE_PATH
$ export CPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH=".../klee-cde-package/cde-root/home/pgbovine/klee/include":$CPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH

Edit the klee-cde-package/bin/* scripts to run:
   cde-exec
intead of:
   $DN/../cde-exec       #  because that is for 32 bits



================================================================================
                                STADY
================================================================================

$ git clone git@git.frama-c.com:gpetiot/pcva.git
$ cd pcva
$ make
$ sudo make install
$ cd ..










I tried to install an up-to-date version of KLEE/LLVM/STP but I failed.
ignore this:
================================================================================
                           KLEE (up-to-date version)
================================================================================

Prerequisites:
$ sudo apt-get install g++ curl python-minimal git bison flex bc libcap-dev gcc-4.8-plugin-dev

STP:
$ svn co -r 1180 https://stp-fast-prover.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/stp-fast-prover/trunk/stp
$ cd stp
$ ./scripts/configure --with-fpic
$ make OPTIMIZE=-O2         #CFLAGS_M32=install        not necessary ?
$ sudo make install
$ ulimit -s unlimited       #run before using STP (and thus KLEE)
$ cd ..

LLVM:
$ sudo apt-get remove llvm llvm-gcc
$ git clone http://llvm.org/git/llvm.git
$ cd llvm
$ ./configure --enable-optimized --enable-assertions
$ make
$ sudo make install
$ cd ..

DRAGONEGG:
$ git clone https://github.com/chapuni/dragonegg.git
$ cd dragonegg
$ make
Add llvm-gcc as an alias to 'gcc -fplugin=./dragonegg.so'
$ cd ..


KLEE:
$ git clone https://github.com/klee/klee.git
$ cd klee
